Notes:

Date: 0/0/1949
Source: Dictionary of the Underworld
Author: PARTRIDGE
Vol / Page: 596
Edition: 1961
Quote: A burglar, or other criminal, that decamps with a confederate's share of the loot: New Zealand since ca. 1920 and, after ca. 1935, Australia: 1932, Nelson Baylis (private letter); 1941, Sidney J. Baker, New Zealnd Slang; 1942, Baker, who defines it also as a `swindler'. Ex Australian and New Zealand (low) s. scale, `to run away'.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 96
Edition:
Quote: <i>scaler</i> robber, especially from his mates; c.1920. ANZ.
